---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import { routes } from '../i18n/routes';
---
<Base
  lang="en"
  pageId="home"
  title="CarveTrace — Provable evidence for high-stakes AI decisions"
  description="Self-hosted, cryptographic evidence for AI decisions. When an audit or dispute happens, your auditor verifies the proof themselves — without trusting you."
>
  <section class="hero">
    <h1>When an AI decision is challenged, can you prove what happened?</h1>
    <p>
      CarveTrace seals every AI decision into a tamper-evident evidence bundle
      that any auditor, regulator, or counterparty can verify themselves —
      without trusting you, and without your data ever leaving your
      infrastructure.
    </p>
    <p>
      <a class="cta" href={routes.demo.en}>See the demo</a>
      &nbsp;
      <a class="cta cta--ghost" href={routes.contact.en}>Request a pilot</a>
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>The day it gets challenged</h2>
    <p>
      An algorithmic decision is disputed. A regulator opens an inquiry. Your
      logs cannot prove what the model saw, when it ran, or what it returned.
      Your word is not evidence.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>What you record, anyone can verify</h2>
    <p>
      CarveTrace captures every event your AI system emits, seals it into a
      cryptographic chain, and timestamps it through an independent RFC 3161
      timestamping authority. The result is an evidence bundle that opens in
      an independent verifier — running in any browser.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Your evidence stays yours</h2>
    <p>
      CarveTrace runs in your infrastructure. We do not host your data. We do
      not see your logs. We do not gate your verifier behind our
      infrastructure — it runs in your browser, on hardware you control, even
      offline. The cryptography is the trust — not us.
    </p>
  </section>
</Base>
